<section style="padding:5rem 1.5rem;max-width:720px;margin:0 auto;">
  <!-- Eyebrow -->
  <p class="fade-in" style="font-family:'Jost',system-ui,sans-serif;font-size:10px;font-weight:500;letter-spacing:0.28em;text-transform:uppercase;color:#c9a84c;margin:0 0 1.25rem;">
    The hook
  </p>

  <!-- H2 -->
  <h2 class="fade-in" style="font-family:'Cormorant Garamond',Georgia,serif;font-weight:500;font-size:clamp(2rem,6vw,3rem);line-height:1.08;letter-spacing:-0.01em;color:#f0ebe0;margin:0 0 2rem;">
    Your friends can make it <em style="color:#c9a84c;font-style:italic;">harder.</em>
  </h2>

  <!-- Body -->
  <div class="fade-in" style="font-family:'Jost',system-ui,sans-serif;font-weight:300;font-size:1rem;line-height:1.75;color:#a39e92;max-width:600px;margin:0 0 2.5rem;">
    <p style="margin:0 0 1.25em;">
      Every morning you draw five cards across Physical, Mental, Nutrition, Recovery, and Wildcard. You commit to two or three.
    </p>
    <p style="margin:0 0 1.25em;">
      Before you finish them, your friends can see what you committed to. A thirty-minute run becomes sixty. Two liters of water becomes three. They can stack bonuses too — call it support — but the deck shifts either way.
    </p>
    <p style="margin:0;">
      Once you complete a card, it's locked. Untouchable. The work is yours.
    </p>
  </div>

  <!-- Pull-quote -->
  <blockquote
    class="fade-in"
    style="font-family:'Cormorant Garamond',Georgia,serif;font-style:italic;font-size:clamp(1.4rem,3.5vw,1.8rem);line-height:1.4;color:#c9a84c;border-left:2px solid #c9a84c;padding-left:1.5rem;margin:0;max-width:500px;"
  >
    "Completed cards are immune. That's the deal."
  </blockquote>
</section>
